Richard D. SHEWMAKER v. Henry Thomas DOUGLAS et al. No. 1320. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Jan. 16, 1936. Thompson, Mitchell, Thompson & Young, of St. Louis, Mo., for appellant. Embry, Johnson, Crowe & Tolbert, of Oklahoma City, Okl., for appellees.

Before LEWIS and BRATTON, Circuit Judges, and KENNEDY, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on motion of appellees.
